content.description: Climb the obvious wide flaring crack until you can pull out onto the face above.  Continue up the face until you reach the top of the pinnacle.  Fun climbing but sort of a novelty route.
content.protection: Trad to #5 Camalot.  Run out face to the top.  No anchor for descent.  Down climb the back or get creative with a rappel off the "summit".
content.location: Located on a stand alone pinnacle in front of the main wall.

content.description: An old project that has been climbed.  A steep short wall with lots of features.  Multiple variations,

Follow the line of bolts up overhanging rock on positive lie-back holds.  Head right and move up on small holds to an airy dino/deadpoint.  A taller person may be able to just grab the edge.  Hand traverse the positive edge and pull up to the slab above.
content.protection: Bolts to a Two bolt anchor

content.description: Two variations to the start, either traveres in from the left using a small crack/edge or climb directly up to the first bolt following a small crack.  Stemming off the ramp to the right is possible, for a harder climb try to avoid this.  Climb past some dirty hold to the clean face above.  Pull the top and descend via Rap hangers
content.protection: Bolts to a two bolt anchor

content.description: A short steep wall with a southern exposure and a great view.
